VSri Sadguru Sangeeta Sabha of Vijayawada presented as its monthly program, a pleasing vocal concert by O.S. Thyagarajan of Chennai at Sri Sivaramakrishna Kshetram. Thyagarajan, a first rank musician, sings in pure traditional style with tuneful and v\u000aibrant voice. His three hour concert was marked by rich repertoire andrakti. The audience were treated to pure classical music.The concert started with a crispvarnaminKedaragowlafollowed by Thyagaraja&#8217;sGurulekainGowrimanohari. One of the major items in the concert wasRajago\u000apalam Bhajeham,a rarekeertanaof Dikshitar inMohana. Thyagarajan adorned it with melody,bhavafilledalapanaand efficientkalpana swaras.There was also exhaustiveniraval. After rendering Syamasastri&#8217;sBirana varalichiinKalyanai,cameChakkani RajamargamudagainKharaharapriya. Sung a\u000as the main piece of the concert, thekeertanacarried an excellent portrait of the raga, pleasingniravaland intricateswaras.Thyagarajan&#8217;smanodharmamaspects amply showed his depth of scholarship. P. Nandakumar who accompanied him on violin followed well and presented a melodious version ofKharaharapriya. Veteran mridangam playe\u000ar M.L.N. Raju gave excellent support on the mridangam and H. Raghu combined well with him on morsing. Thyagarajan&#8217;s concert came to close with aThyagaraja Utsava Sampradaya keertanainNeelambari -Uyyalalugavayya -and a bhajan.
